{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1777073996784,"sessionID":"ses_23e23a62affeOLCYKs5at8IiBV","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_35uFRBPJckOMCM2PBnDETmJ4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\mycli\\README.md","limit":220,"offset":1},"output":"<path>D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\mycli\\README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # mycli\n2: \n3: `mycli` 是 `D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library` 的统一命令入口。\n4: \n5: 它把能力包、脚本、现有 CLI 工具组织成一套可发现、可说明、可执行的命令体系。\n6: \n7: ## Usage\n8: \n9: ```powershell\n10: mycli --help\n11: mycli list\n12: mycli package list\n13: mycli package register <package/path> --summary <text> --source <text>\n14: mycli package register-full <package/path> --summary <text> --source <text> --commands <json> --help <markdown>\n15: mycli <package...> --help\n16: mycli <package...> list\n17: mycli <package...> command list\n18: mycli <package...> command register <name> --summary <text> --entry <absolute-path> --args <json> [--prefix-args <json>]\n19: mycli <package...> command register-many --commands <json>\n20: mycli <package...> command update <name> [--summary <text>] [--entry <absolute-path>] [--args <json>] [--prefix-args <json>]\n21: mycli <package...> help update --content <markdown>\n22: mycli <package...> <command> [args...]\n23: ```\n24: \n25: ## Core Ideas\n26: \n27: - `package`\n28:   一个能力包\n29: - `subpackage`\n30:   包下面的子包，目录即层级\n31: - `command`\n32:   包里的具体执行动作\n33: - `cli.package.json`\n34:   包注册中心\n35: - `README.md`\n36:   包级帮助内容来源\n37: \n38: ## Common Flows\n39: \n40: 查看所有顶层包：\n41: \n42: ```powershell\n43: mycli list\n44: ```\n45: \n46: 查看某个包的完整说明：\n47: \n48: ```powershell\n49: mycli opencode --help\n50: ```\n51: \n52: 查看某个包里有哪些子包和命令：\n53: \n54: ```powershell\n55: mycli opencode list\n56: ```\n57: \n58: 执行某个命令：\n59: \n60: ```powershell\n61: mycli opencode run \"hello\"\n62: ```\n63: \n64: 查看并使用 workflow 能力：\n65: \n66: ```powershell\n67: mycli agent-workflow --help\n68: mycli agent-workflow list\n69: mycli agent-workflow validate D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\agent-system-rules\\agent-workflow\\examples\\script_echo_flow\n70: ```\n71: \n72: ## opencode Example\n73: \n74: `opencode` 目前同时支持两种方式：\n75: \n76: 直接映射命令：\n77: \n78: ```powershell\n79: mycli opencode run \"hello\"\n80: mycli opencode models --help\n81: mycli opencode agent --help\n82: ```\n83: \n84: 原生透传：\n85: \n86: ```powershell\n87: mycli opencode native --help\n88: mycli opencode native run hello\n89: mycli opencode native models --help\n90: ```\n91: \n92: ## agent-workflow Example\n93: \n94: `agent-workflow` 适合把多步骤任务建模成可运行、可等待、可审核的 workflow。\n95: \n96: ```powershell\n97: mycli agent-workflow init D:\\agent_workspace\\projects\\my-flow --workflow-id my_flow --name \"My Flow\"\n98: mycli agent-workflow scaffold D:\\agent_workspace\\projects\\my-flow\n99: mycli agent-workflow validate D:\\agent_workspace\\projects\\my-flow\n100: mycli agent-workflow graph D:\\agent_workspace\\projects\\my-flow\n101: mycli agent-workflow start-run D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\agent-system-rules\\agent-workflow\\examples\\script_echo_flow\n102: ```\n103: \n104: 单次 agent 调用优先用 `mycli agent-cli run`。\n105: 多步骤、可等待、可审核、带运行状态的流程优先用 `mycli agent-workflow ...`。\n106: \n107: ## Docs\n108: \n109: 用户手册：\n110: \n111: - `D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\mycli\\common\\user-manual.md`\n112: \n113: 维护与技术手册：\n114: \n115: - `D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\mycli\\common\\technical-manual.md`\n\n(End of file - total 115 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# mycli\n\n`mycli` 是 `D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library` 的统一命令入口。\n\n它把能力包、脚本、现有 CLI 工具组织成一套可发现、可说明、可执行的命令体系。\n\n## Usage\n\n```powershell\nmycli --help\nmycli list\nmycli package list\nmycli package register <package/path> --summary <text> --source <text>\nmycli package register-full <package/path> --summary <text> --source <text> --commands <json> --help <markdown>\nmycli <package...> --help\nmycli <package...> list\nmycli <package...> command list\nmycli <package...> command register <name> --summary <text> --entry <absolute-path> --args <json> [--prefix-args <json>]\nmycli <package...> command register-many --commands <json>\nmycli <package...> command update <name> [--summary <text>] [--entry <absolute-path>] [--args <json>] [--prefix-args <json>]","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"agent_workspace\\capability-library\\mycli\\README.md","time":{"start":1777073996771,"end":1777073996783}},"id":"prt_dc1dd43de001DmPrC1H24XXglV","sessionID":"ses_23e23a62affeOLCYKs5at8IiBV","messageID":"msg_dc1dd0da000139Jy0EFNMApPNv"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1777073996840,"sessionID":"ses_23e23a62affeOLCYKs5at8IiBV","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_E0nLUYEIiY2KrWCU2QxUsyqO","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\mycli\\common\\technical-manual.md","limit":260,"offset":1},"output":"<path>D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\mycli\\common\\technical-manual.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # mycli 维护与技术手册\n2: \n3: ## 1. 文档目的\n4: \n5: 这份文档面向后续维护 `mycli` 的技术人员。\n6: \n7: 目标是帮助后续继续做这些事情：\n8: \n9: - 新增能力包\n10: - 调整命令注册结构\n11: - 修改帮助展示逻辑\n12: - 接入已有外部 CLI\n13: - 排查运行时问题\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## 2. 当前目录结构\n18: \n19: 当前根目录：\n20: \n21: ```text\n22: D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\mycli\n23: ```\n24: \n25: 关键文件：\n26: \n27: - `mycli.ps1`\n28:   PowerShell 主入口包装器\n29: - `mycli.cmd`\n30:   Windows 命令行包装器\n31: - `common\\cli.ps1`\n32:   核心运行时实现\n33: - `common\\requirements.md`\n34:   需求与设计收敛文档\n35: - `common\\user-manual.md`\n36:   面向用户的使用手册\n37: - `common\\technical-manual.md`\n38:   本文档\n39: \n40: 包目录示例：\n41: \n42: ```text\n43: mycli\\\n44:   opencode\\\n45:     cli.package.json\n46:     README.md\n47: ```\n48: \n49: ---\n50: \n51: ## 3. 核心设计模型\n52: \n53: `mycli` 的核心对象有 4 类：\n54: \n55: - `package`\n56:   能力包\n57: - `subpackage`\n58:   子包，目录即层级\n59: - `command`\n60:   包内可执行命令\n61: - `help`\n62:   包级文档，来自 `README.md`\n63: \n64: 核心设计原则：\n65: \n66: - 包树使用目录结构表示\n67: - 每个包目录使用 `cli.package.json` 作为注册中心\n68: - 每个包目录使用 `README.md` 作为 `--help` 数据源\n69: - `entry` 统一使用绝对路径\n70: - 命令参数采用结构化 `args`\n71: - 外部 CLI 可以通过“直接转发”或“前缀转发”接入\n72: \n73: ---\n74: \n75: ## 4. 运行时职责分层\n76: \n77: ### `mycli.ps1`\n78: \n79: 负责把用户输入传给核心脚本：\n80: \n81: - 作为 PowerShell 入口\n82: - 调用 `common\\cli.ps1`\n83: \n84: ### `mycli.cmd`\n85: \n86: 负责兼容 `cmd` 场景：\n87: \n88: - 作为批处理入口\n89: - 再转到 PowerShell 入口\n90: \n91: ### `common\\cli.ps1`\n92: \n93: 这是整个系统的核心。\n94: \n95: 主要职责：\n96: \n97: - 参数解析\n98: - 路径与包定位\n99: - 包配置读取与写入\n100: - 命令注册与更新\n101: - README 帮助读取与写入\n102: - 已注册命令的实际执行\n103: \n104: ---\n105: \n106: ## 5. 包结构约定\n107: \n108: 任意包目录都应当至少包含：\n109: \n110: - `cli.package.json`\n111: - `README.md`\n112: \n113: 示例：\n114: \n115: ```text\n116: D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\mycli\\opencode\\\n117:   cli.package.json\n118:   README.md\n119: ```\n120: \n121: 嵌套包示例：\n122: \n123: ```text\n124: D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\mycli\\dev\\\n125:   cli.package.json\n126:   README.md\n127:   opencli\\\n128:     cli.package.json\n129:     README.md\n130: ```\n131: \n132: ---\n133: \n134: ## 6. `cli.package.json` 结构\n135: \n136: 当前最核心字段：\n137: \n138: ```json\n139: {\n140:   \"name\": \"opencode\",\n141:   \"summary\": \"Forwarding package for the existing opencode CLI\",\n142:   \"source\": \"D:\\\\agent_workspace\\\\projects\\\\opencode\",\n143:   \"commands\": [\n144:     {\n145:       \"name\": \"run\",\n146:       \"summary\": \"Run opencode with a message\",\n147:       \"args\": [\n148:         {\n149:           \"name\": \"message\",\n150:           \"required\": false,\n151:           \"summary\": \"Message to send to opencode\",\n152:           \"type\": \"string\"\n153:         }\n154:       ],\n155:       \"prefixArgs\": [\n156:         \"run\"\n157:       ],\n158:       \"entry\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\38188\\\\AppData\\\\Roaming\\\\npm\\\\opencode.ps1\"\n159:     }\n160:   ]\n161: }\n162: ```\n163: \n164: 字段说明：\n165: \n166: - `name`\n167:   包名，通常等于目录名\n168: - `summary`\n169:   顶层 `list` 或子包展示时的一句话简介\n170: - `source`\n171:   来源描述，推荐绝对路径，也允许自定义文本\n172: - `commands`\n173:   命令注册数组\n174: \n175: 命令对象字段：\n176: \n177: - `name`\n178:   命令名\n179: - `summary`\n180:   命令简介\n181: - `args`\n182:   结构化参数说明\n183: - `entry`\n184:   绝对路径入口\n185: - `prefixArgs`\n186:   可选。固定插入到实际执行前面的参数数组\n187: \n188: ---\n189: \n190: ## 7. `prefixArgs` 的作用\n191: \n192: 这是当前支持“原生 CLI 包装”的关键机制。\n193: \n194: ### 直接透传\n195: \n196: 例如：\n197: \n198: ```json\n199: {\n200:   \"name\": \"native\",\n201:   \"summary\": \"Forward all remaining arguments to opencode\",\n202:   \"args\": [],\n203:   \"entry\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\38188\\\\AppData\\\\Roaming\\\\npm\\\\opencode.ps1\"\n204: }\n205: ```\n206: \n207: 此时：\n208: \n209: ```powershell\n210: mycli opencode native run hello\n211: ```\n212: \n213: 会执行：\n214: \n215: ```powershell\n216: opencode run hello\n217: ```\n218: \n219: ### 前缀转发\n220: \n221: 例如：\n222: \n223: ```json\n224: {\n225:   \"name\": \"run\",\n226:   \"summary\": \"Run opencode with a message\",\n227:   \"args\": [],\n228:   \"prefixArgs\": [\"run\"],\n229:   \"entry\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\38188\\\\AppData\\\\Roaming\\\\npm\\\\opencode.ps1\"\n230: }\n231: ```\n232: \n233: 此时：\n234: \n235: ```powershell\n236: mycli opencode run hello\n237: ```\n238: \n239: 会执行：\n240: \n241: ```powershell\n242: opencode run hello\n243: ```\n244: \n245: 所以：\n246: \n247: - `native` 适合原样透传\n248: - `prefixArgs` 适合把原生子命令重定义成 `mycli` 的直接命令\n249: \n250: ---\n251: \n252: ## 8. 当前命令行为\n253: \n254: ### 顶层\n255: \n256: - `mycli --help`\n257: - `mycli list`\n258: - `mycli package list`\n259: - `mycli package register`\n260: - `mycli package register-full`\n\n(Showing lines 1-260 of 525. Use offset=261 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# mycli 维护与技术手册\n\n## 1. 文档目的\n\n这份文档面向后续维护 `mycli` 的技术人员。\n\n目标是帮助后续继续做这些事情：\n\n- 新增能力包\n- 调整命令注册结构\n- 修改帮助展示逻辑\n- 接入已有外部 CLI\n- 排查运行时问题\n\n---\n\n## 2. 当前目录结构\n\n当前根目录：\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"agent_workspace\\capability-library\\mycli\\common\\technical-manual.md","time":{"start":1777073996825,"end":1777073996840}},"id":"prt_dc1dd43f0001GVeFyEL8cEi1Rh","sessionID":"ses_23e23a62affeOLCYKs5at8IiBV","messageID":"msg_dc1dd0da000139Jy0EFNMApPNv"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1777073996899,"sessionID":"ses_23e23a62affeOLCYKs5at8IiBV","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_62vHneLV70YQk6bJFZzaODMu","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\skill-library\\task-hall\\SKILL.md","limit":260,"offset":1},"output":"<path>D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\skill-library\\task-hall\\SKILL.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: name: task-hall\n3: description: \"Use when an agent needs to publish, inspect, claim, report, or review tasks through the local mycli task-hall. Covers frontdesk-v0.2 JSON task requests, Markdown task specs, model-tier claim gates, reviewer-v0.1 task reports, and safe task lifecycle conventions.\"\n4: ---\n5: \n6: # Task Hall Skill\n7: \n8: ## Purpose\n9: \n10: Use this skill when working with the local agent task hall:\n11: \n12: ```powershell\n13: mycli task-hall ...\n14: ```\n15: \n16: `task-hall` is a task coordination surface. It does not execute worker tasks and does not actively dispatch worker agents. It stores task requests, generated task Markdown, listings, claims, reports, frontdesk decisions, and reviewer decisions.\n17: \n18: Current protocol versions:\n19: \n20: - Frontdesk: `frontdesk-v0.2`\n21: - Reviewer: `reviewer-v0.1`\n22: \n23: Agent definitions:\n24: \n25: ```text\n26: C:\\Users\\38188\\.config\\opencode\\agent\\task-hall-frontdesk.md\n27: C:\\Users\\38188\\.config\\opencode\\agent\\task-hall-reviewer.md\n28: ```\n29: \n30: Package docs and implementation:\n31: \n32: ```text\n33: D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\mycli\\task-hall\\README.md\n34: D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\mycli\\task-hall\\scripts\\task-hall.ps1\n35: ```\n36: \n37: ## Current Implementation Status\n38: \n39: The current implementation has been tested end-to-end:\n40: \n41: - `submit-request` calls `agent-cli` and runs `opencode/task-hall-frontdesk`.\n42: - The frontdesk agent reviews task request JSON and returns JSON.\n43: - Accepted requests create a task `task.md` containing `## 领取门槛`.\n44: - `submit-request` creates a `listed` task by default; `--draft` creates a draft.\n45: - `claim` calls the frontdesk agent to evaluate a claim request against the Markdown claim gate.\n46: - `review-submission` calls `opencode/task-hall-reviewer` to evaluate a task report.\n47: - Reviewer decisions can mark complete, return to the same agent, relist as-is, or revise and relist.\n48: - `tasks all --json` returns JSON output.\n49: \n50: ## Commands\n51: \n52: Initialize and inspect:\n53: \n54: ```powershell\n55: mycli task-hall init\n56: mycli task-hall tasks\n57: mycli task-hall tasks all\n58: mycli task-hall tasks all --json\n59: mycli task-hall show <task-id>\n60: mycli task-hall status\n61: ```\n62: \n63: Publish through the frontdesk:\n64: \n65: ```powershell\n66: mycli task-hall submit-request D:\\agent_workspace\\tmp\\task-request.json\n67: mycli task-hall submit-request D:\\agent_workspace\\tmp\\task-request.json --draft\n68: ```\n69: \n70: Claim through the frontdesk:\n71: \n72: ```powershell\n73: mycli task-hall claim <task-id> opencode/private-assistant D:\\agent_workspace\\tmp\\claim.json\n74: ```\n75: \n76: Submit a report for reviewer decision:\n77: \n78: ```powershell\n79: mycli task-hall review-submission <task-id> D:\\agent_workspace\\tmp\\task-report.md\n80: ```\n81: \n82: Compatibility commands:\n83: \n84: ```powershell\n85: mycli task-hall upload D:\\path\\task.md custom 50 \"tag1,tag2\" \"任务标题\"\n86: mycli task-hall upload-publish D:\\path\\task.md custom 50 \"tag1,tag2\" \"任务标题\"\n87: mycli task-hall publish <task-id>\n88: mycli task-hall release <task-id> <agent-id>\n89: mycli task-hall submit <task-id> success <agent-id> \"完成说明\"\n90: mycli task-hall submit <task-id> fail <agent-id> \"失败说明\"\n91: ```\n92: \n93: Prefer the frontdesk/reviewer workflow for normal use. Use compatibility commands for migration, smoke tests, or explicitly requested manual operations.\n94: \n95: ## Publish Task Request Standard\n96: \n97: Agents should publish tasks by submitting a JSON request, not by directly uploading hand-written Markdown, unless explicitly asked.\n98: \n99: Minimum task request JSON:\n100: \n101: ```json\n102: {\n103:   \"request_type\": \"custom\",\n104:   \"title\": \"任务标题\",\n105:   \"requester\": \"opencode/private-assistant\",\n106:   \"description\": \"要完成什么\",\n107:   \"context\": \"为什么要做、已有背景、相关路径或系统\",\n108:   \"expected_output\": \"期望交付物\",\n109:   \"constraints\": [\n110:     \"约束 1\",\n111:     \"约束 2\"\n112:   ]\n113: }\n114: ```\n115: \n116: Allowed `request_type` values:\n117: \n118: - `scheduled`: periodic task.\n119: - `trigger`: event-triggered task.\n120: - `custom`: one-off custom task.\n121: \n122: Useful optional fields:\n123: \n124: ```json\n125: {\n126:   \"target_path\": \"D:\\\\agent_workspace\\\\...\",\n127:   \"schedule\": \"daily 09:00\",\n128:   \"trigger\": \"当某事件发生时\",\n129:   \"priority\": 50,\n130:   \"tags\": [\"task-hall\", \"docs\"]\n131: }\n132: ```\n133: \n134: Quality rules:\n135: \n136: - The goal must be clear.\n137: - The context must be sufficient for another agent.\n138: - Expected output must be explicit.\n139: - Constraints must include safety boundaries.\n140: - Scheduled tasks must include schedule/frequency and output location.\n141: - Trigger tasks must include trigger condition, input event, and output action.\n142: - Risky actions such as delete, push, deploy, publish, external writes, credential handling, paid services, or account changes require explicit authorization boundaries.\n143: \n144: If frontdesk rejects the request, read the generated `frontdesk-response.json`, fix missing information, and submit a new request.\n145: \n146: ## Claim Request Standard\n147: \n148: Before claiming, read the task:\n149: \n150: ```powershell\n151: mycli task-hall show <task-id>\n152: ```\n153: \n154: Then submit a claim JSON:\n155: \n156: ```json\n157: {\n158:   \"task_id\": \"task_...\",\n159:   \"agent_id\": \"opencode/private-assistant\",\n160:   \"model\": \"MoreCode/gpt-5.5\",\n161:   \"model_tier\": \"expert\",\n162:   \"claim_reason\": \"我已阅读任务，模型等级满足领取门槛，准备立即处理。\"\n163: }\n164: ```\n165: \n166: Model tier order:\n167: \n168: ```text\n169: nano < cheap < standard < strong < expert\n170: ```\n171: \n172: Claim gate rules:\n173: \n174: - Frontdesk reads the task Markdown `## 领取门槛`.\n175: - `model_tier` must satisfy the minimum model requirement.\n176: - Skill tags are not hard requirements in v0.2.\n177: - Do not claim tasks you are not ready to work on.\n178: - `--no-frontdesk` is only for maintainer testing or exception repair.\n179: \n180: ## Task Report Standard\n181: \n182: When work is done, partially done, blocked, or impossible, submit a Markdown report through the reviewer:\n183: \n184: ```powershell\n185: mycli task-hall review-submission <task-id> D:\\agent_workspace\\tmp\\task-report.md\n186: ```\n187: \n188: Report template:\n189: \n190: ```markdown\n191: # 任务报告\n192: \n193: ## 任务结论\n194: \n195: 完成 / 部分完成 / 受阻 / 无法完成\n196: \n197: ## 完成内容\n198: \n199: - ...\n200: \n201: ## 未完成内容\n202: \n203: - ...\n204: \n205: ## 产物路径\n206: \n207: - `D:\\path\\to\\artifact`\n208: \n209: ## 验证结果\n210: \n211: - 执行了什么命令或检查\n212: - 结果是什么\n213: - 如果没有验证，说明原因\n214: \n215: ## 遇到的问题\n216: \n217: - ...\n218: \n219: ## 是否需要继续\n220: \n221: - 不需要，任务已完成\n222: - 需要，建议继续做 ...\n223: - 无法继续，原因是 ...\n224: ```\n225: \n226: Completion reports must include:\n227: \n228: - Point-by-point response to the original goal.\n229: - Point-by-point response to requested deliverables.\n230: - Artifact paths or explicit non-file output description.\n231: - Verification method and result.\n232: - Clear statement that no key items remain unfinished.\n233: \n234: Blocked or partial reports must include:\n235: \n236: - Completed parts.\n237: - Remaining parts.\n238: - Blocking reason.\n239: - Attempts already made.\n240: - Intermediate artifact paths.\n241: - Recommended next step.\n242: - Whether the task should be revised, split, relisted, or have its model gate raised.\n243: \n244: Do not submit low-information reports such as only `ok`, `done`, or `failed`.\n245: \n246: ## Reviewer Decisions\n247: \n248: The reviewer agent returns one of:\n249: \n250: - `complete`: task is done; task-hall marks it `done`.\n251: - `return_to_agent`: report is insufficient or work incomplete; original agent should continue.\n252: - `relist_as_is`: task is still valid and should be relisted without changing `task.md`.\n253: - `revise_and_relist`: task Markdown is revised based on current progress/blockers and relisted.\n254: \n255: The reviewer does not execute commands, inspect files deeply, or fix the work. It judges text consistency between the original task and the report.\n256: \n257: ## Safety Rules\n258: \n259: - Task-hall is not user authorization for risky operations.\n260: - Do not hide dangerous effects in vague descriptions.\n\n(Showing lines 1-260 of 264. Use offset=261 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\nname: task-hall\ndescription: \"Use when an agent needs to publish, inspect, claim, report, or review tasks through the local mycli task-hall. Covers frontdesk-v0.2 JSON task requests, Markdown task specs, model-tier claim gates, reviewer-v0.1 task reports, and safe task lifecycle conventions.\"\n---\n\n# Task Hall Skill\n\n## Purpose\n\nUse this skill when working with the local agent task hall:\n\n```powershell\nmycli task-hall ...\n```\n\n`task-hall` is a task coordination surface. It does not execute worker tasks and does not actively dispatch worker agents. It stores task requests, generated task Markdown, listings, claims, reports, frontdesk decisions, and reviewer decisions.\n\nCurrent protocol versions:\n\n- Frontdesk: `frontdesk-v0.2`","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"agent_workspace\\capability-library\\skill-library\\task-hall\\SKILL.md","time":{"start":1777073996886,"end":1777073996898}},"id":"prt_dc1dd441f001sq2skpAOlTBdG5","sessionID":"ses_23e23a62affeOLCYKs5at8IiBV","messageID":"msg_dc1dd0da000139Jy0EFNMApPNv"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1777073997004,"sessionID":"ses_23e23a62affeOLCYKs5at8IiBV","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_Xxhe71yyvMDgNgIvDGh1HgMR","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\skill-library\\project-manager\\SKILL.md","limit":220,"offset":1},"output":"<path>D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\skill-library\\project-manager\\SKILL.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: name: project-manager\n3: description: \"Project manager rule package for durable agent-managed projects. Use when registering projects, querying projects by name/type/status/lifecycle/phase/health/tags, managing current project status, tracking next actions, or modeling ongoing projects such as asset libraries and daily collection jobs under D:\\\\agent_workspace.\"\n4: ---\n5: \n6: # Project Manager\n7: \n8: ## Purpose\n9: \n10: Use this capability when work should be managed as a durable project instead of a one-off chat task.\n11: \n12: This package is centered on:\n13: \n14: - per-project `.agent-project/project.json` files as source of truth\n15: - `.agent-project/status.md` as the human-readable status page\n16: - project registry and query index files\n17: - project lifecycle, phase, activity, health, delivery, and attention fields\n18: - finite projects and ongoing projects\n19: - current task and next-action tracking\n20: - task and next-action files that can be updated from `mycli`\n21: - dynamic context entries for requirements, feasibility, architecture, construction, validation, operations, maintenance, and handoff\n22: - agent takeover guides and maintenance guides generated from project state\n23: - ongoing operations snapshots for scheduled/manual/daemon-like projects\n24: \n25: ## Primary Entrypoints\n26: \n27: Prefer:\n28: \n29: ```powershell\n30: mycli project-manager ...\n31: ```\n32: \n33: Direct entrypoints:\n34: \n35: ```powershell\n36: D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\agent-system-rules\\project-manager\\scripts\\project-manager.ps1 <command> ...\n37: python D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\agent-system-rules\\project-manager\\src\\project_manager.py <command> ...\n38: ```\n39: \n40: ## Use This When\n41: \n42: - registering a project into the agent workspace\n43: - querying projects by name, status, lifecycle, phase, type, owner, tags, or attention flags\n44: - updating a project's current status or current next action\n45: - modeling a continuous/ongoing project such as a material library, daily news collection, monitoring, or recurring report pipeline\n46: - deciding whether a project is finite (`finite`) or ongoing (`ongoing`)\n47: - creating a handoff/status summary for later continuation\n48: - handing a project to another agent or another session\n49: - recording new project context that should survive beyond the current chat\n50: - linking a project to workflows, skills, repositories, or artifacts\n51: \n52: ## Recommended Flow\n53: \n54: ```powershell\n55: mycli project-manager init D:\\agent_workspace\\projects\\my-project --id my-project --name \"My Project\" --type coding --mode finite --register\n56: mycli project-manager query --lifecycle active\n57: mycli project-manager task-add my-project --title \"Implement first feature\" --type implement --set-current\n58: mycli project-manager next-add my-project --title \"Run validation\" --type validate --set-current\n59: mycli project-manager update-status my-project --lifecycle active --phase construction --activity in_progress --delivery draft --summary \"Implementation started.\"\n60: mycli project-manager get my-project\n61: mycli project-manager status my-project\n62: ```\n63: \n64: ## Command Quick Reference\n65: \n66: Discovery and registration:\n67: \n68: ```powershell\n69: mycli project-manager init <project-root> --id <id> --name <name> --type <type> --mode finite|ongoing [--register]\n70: mycli project-manager register <project-root>\n71: mycli project-manager scan [roots...]\n72: mycli project-manager refresh [roots...]\n73: ```\n74: \n75: Query and status:\n76: \n77: ```powershell\n78: mycli project-manager list\n79: mycli project-manager query --name <text>\n80: mycli project-manager query --type capability\n81: mycli project-manager query --mode ongoing\n82: mycli project-manager query --lifecycle active --phase operations\n83: mycli project-manager query --health red --attention needs_maintenance\n84: mycli project-manager get <id-or-name>\n85: mycli project-manager status <id-or-name>\n86: ```\n87: \n88: Maintenance:\n89: \n90: ```powershell\n91: mycli project-manager update-status <id> --phase validation --activity in_progress --health green --summary \"...\"\n92: mycli project-manager task-list <id>\n93: mycli project-manager task-add <id> --title \"...\" --type implement --priority high --set-current\n94: mycli project-manager task-update <id> task-0001 --status done\n95: mycli project-manager next-list <id>\n96: mycli project-manager next-add <id> --title \"...\" --type decide --set-current\n97: mycli project-manager next-update <id> next-0001 --status done\n98: mycli project-manager context-add <id> --title \"Validation finding\" --phase validation --summary \"...\"\n99: mycli project-manager current <id>\n100: mycli project-manager agent-guide <id>\n101: mycli project-manager maintenance-guide <id>\n102: ```\n103: \n104: ## Core Model\n105: \n106: Each project owns:\n107: \n108: ```text\n109: .agent-project/\n110:   project.json\n111:   status.md\n112:   tasks/\n113:   next-actions/\n114:   decisions/\n115:   context/\n116:   operations/\n117:   runs/\n118:   handoffs/\n119: ```\n120: \n121: Global query uses a generated registry:\n122: \n123: ```text\n124: D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\mycli\\project-manager\\registry.json\n125: ```\n126: \n127: `project.json` is the truth. `registry.json` is a query cache and can be rebuilt.\n128: \n129: ## Project Types\n130: \n131: Supported `project_type` values:\n132: \n133: - `capability` — capability-library or agent-system-rules capability package\n134: - `workflow` — agent-workflow project\n135: - `coding` — ordinary code project\n136: - `research` — research or information gathering project\n137: - `documentation` — docs, knowledge base, material library\n138: - `ops` — operations/environment project\n139: - `experiment` — temporary experiment\n140: - `external_repo` — external mirrored/cloned repository\n141: - `meta` — agent system / prompt / workspace governance work\n142: \n143: Supported `project_mode` values:\n144: \n145: - `finite` — finite delivery project; can become `completed`\n146: - `ongoing` — continuous/operational project; should eventually become `retired`, not `completed`\n147: \n148: ## Status Axes\n149: \n150: Project status is intentionally multi-axis:\n151: \n152: - `project_mode`: `finite | ongoing`\n153: - `lifecycle`: `proposed | planned | active | paused | completed | retired | archived`\n154: - `phase`: `intake | requirements | feasibility | architecture | planning | construction | validation | launch | operations | maintenance | retirement | closure`\n155: - `activity`: `queued | in_progress | scheduled | stable | running | waiting | blocked | degraded | paused | needs_attention`\n156: - `health`: `green | yellow | red | gray`\n157: - `delivery`: `none | concept | draft | prototype | usable | delivered | verified | published | deprecated`\n158: \n159: Important rules:\n160: \n161: - `ongoing` projects should not be marked `completed`; they end as `retired`.\n162: - ongoing projects normally live in `lifecycle=active`, `phase=operations`, and `activity=stable/running/scheduled`.\n163: - `phase=maintenance` is a normal phase, not a failure state.\n164: - Use `activity=degraded` when an ongoing project still runs but has partial failures or quality degradation.\n165: - Use `attention[]` for user/agent queues such as `needs_user_decision`, `needs_validation`, or `needs_maintenance`.\n166: \n167: ## Dynamic Context and Agent Takeover\n168: \n169: Use dynamic context commands to capture changing project context by phase:\n170: \n171: ```powershell\n172: mycli project-manager context-add <project> --title \"Requirement boundary\" --phase requirements --type requirement --summary \"...\"\n173: mycli project-manager context-add <project> --title \"Architecture note\" --phase architecture --type architecture --summary \"...\" --file README.md\n174: mycli project-manager context-list <project> --phase validation\n175: mycli project-manager context-get <project> context-0001\n176: ```\n177: \n178: When an agent team takes over a project, use:\n179: \n180: ```powershell\n181: mycli project-manager current <project>\n182: mycli project-manager agent-guide <project>\n183: mycli project-manager agent-guide <project> --phase <phase>\n184: mycli project-manager maintenance-guide <project>\n185: ```\n186: \n187: `agent-guide` is the primary handoff surface. It includes project identity, management rules, maintenance rules, current status, open tasks, open next actions, and phase-specific dynamic context.\n188: \n189: ### Dynamic Context Rules\n190: \n191: Add dynamic context whenever important project knowledge would otherwise remain only in chat history. Good candidates include:\n192: \n193: - requirements and scope boundaries from the user\n194: - feasibility risks and rejected alternatives\n195: - architecture decisions or implementation constraints\n196: - validation results and reproduction notes\n197: - ongoing operation incidents or schedule changes\n198: - maintenance rules, compatibility constraints, and retirement criteria\n199: \n200: Prefer one clear entry per fact or decision context. Always choose a meaningful `--phase` and `--type`, and attach relevant files with `--file` when useful.\n201: \n202: ### Agent Takeover Rules\n203: \n204: When taking over an existing project:\n205: \n206: 1. Run `mycli project-manager current <project>`.\n207: 2. Run `mycli project-manager agent-guide <project>`.\n208: 3. If the work is phase-specific, rerun `agent-guide` with `--phase <phase>`.\n209: 4. For ongoing or maintenance work, run `mycli project-manager maintenance-guide <project>`.\n210: 5. Update task, next-action, status, and dynamic context after meaningful progress.\n211: \n212: Do not rely only on previous chat history; `.agent-project/project.json`, task files, next-action files, and context entries are the durable source.\n213: \n214: ## When Maintaining Project Manager Itself\n215: \n216: The source package is:\n217: \n218: ```text\n219: D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\agent-system-rules\\project-manager\n220: ```\n\n(Showing lines 1-220 of 234. Use offset=221 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\nname: project-manager\ndescription: \"Project manager rule package for durable agent-managed projects. Use when registering projects, querying projects by name/type/status/lifecycle/phase/health/tags, managing current project status, tracking next actions, or modeling ongoing projects such as asset libraries and daily collection jobs under D:\\\\agent_workspace.\"\n---\n\n# Project Manager\n\n## Purpose\n\nUse this capability when work should be managed as a durable project instead of a one-off chat task.\n\nThis package is centered on:\n\n- per-project `.agent-project/project.json` files as source of truth\n- `.agent-project/status.md` as the human-readable status page\n- project registry and query index files\n- project lifecycle, phase, activity, health, delivery, and attention fields\n- finite projects and ongoing projects\n- current task and next-action tracking\n- task and next-action files that can be updated from `mycli`","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"agent_workspace\\capability-library\\skill-library\\project-manager\\SKILL.md","time":{"start":1777073996991,"end":1777073997003}},"id":"prt_dc1dd445b001Z2p35m1FlxE4uf","sessionID":"ses_23e23a62affeOLCYKs5at8IiBV","messageID":"msg_dc1dd0da000139Jy0EFNMApPNv"}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1777073997037,"sessionID":"ses_23e23a62affeOLCYKs5at8IiBV","part":{"id":"prt_dc1dd44eb0010b417ibSLe2P25","reason":"tool-calls","messageID":"msg_dc1dd0da000139Jy0EFNMApPNv","sessionID":"ses_23e23a62affeOLCYKs5at8IiBV","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":28585,"input":311,"output":498,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":27776}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1777074016594,"sessionID":"ses_23e23a62affeOLCYKs5at8IiBV","part":{"id":"prt_dc1dd9151001kCZMMD0FJ07jLX","messageID":"msg_dc1dd44ef001kVrCHLqkpcf6ae","sessionID":"ses_23e23a62affeOLCYKs5at8IiBV","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1777074016679,"sessionID":"ses_23e23a62affeOLCYKs5at8IiBV","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_frgNKsvJ8g6dhrVfYQZHTfVa","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\mycli\\task-hall\\README.md","limit":260,"offset":1},"output":"<path>D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\mycli\\task-hall\\README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # task-hall\n2: \n3: 当前任务前台协议版本：`frontdesk-v0.2`\n4: \n5: `task-hall` 是面向 agent 的任务大厅。它只负责任务从“提交/上传”到“上架、展示、领取记录、报告审核、关闭或重新上架”的生命周期，不负责执行任务，也不主动调度任务。\n6: \n7: ## Design\n8: \n9: 任务大厅支持三类任务请求来源：\n10: \n11: - `scheduled`：定时定点发布到大厅的任务。\n12: - `trigger`：外部条件满足后发布到大厅的任务；条件检查由用户自定义 trigger 负责。\n13: - `custom`：手动上传和上架的临时任务。\n14: \n15: 任务请求入口推荐使用 JSON；通过前台 agent 审核后生成 Markdown 任务说明文件，推荐命名为 `task.md`。任务正文、约束、交付物、验收标准和领取门槛以 Markdown 为主体。\n16: \n17: 前台 agent 与审核 agent 配置位于：\n18: \n19: ```text\n20: C:\\Users\\38188\\.config\\opencode\\agent\\task-hall-frontdesk.md\n21: C:\\Users\\38188\\.config\\opencode\\agent\\task-hall-reviewer.md\n22: ```\n23: \n24: ## Frontdesk v0.2 Protocol\n25: \n26: `frontdesk-v0.2` 采用“轻 JSON 入口 + Markdown 语义协议”的设计：\n27: \n28: - 任务提交时，上交任务请求 JSON。\n29: - 前台 agent 判断任务是否可接受、描述是否完整。\n30: - 不完整则退回，要求发起 agent 重新提交任务请求。\n31: - 通过后由前台 agent 生成 `task.md`。\n32: - `task.md` 中必须包含 `## 领取门槛`，写明复杂度和最低模型要求。\n33: - agent 领取时提交领取申请 JSON。\n34: - 前台 agent 根据 `task.md` 的领取门槛和领取申请中的模型等级判断是否允许领取。\n35: - skill 不作为第一版硬性领取条件。\n36: \n37: ### Task Request JSON\n38: \n39: 任务请求 JSON 最小结构：\n40: \n41: ```json\n42: {\n43:   \"request_type\": \"scheduled | trigger | custom\",\n44:   \"title\": \"任务标题\",\n45:   \"requester\": \"请求发起方\",\n46:   \"description\": \"任务描述\",\n47:   \"context\": \"背景上下文\",\n48:   \"expected_output\": \"期望交付物\",\n49:   \"constraints\": []\n50: }\n51: ```\n52: \n53: 可选字段：\n54: \n55: ```json\n56: {\n57:   \"target_path\": \"目标路径\",\n58:   \"schedule\": \"定时规则，仅 scheduled 需要\",\n59:   \"trigger\": \"触发条件，仅 trigger 需要\",\n60:   \"priority\": 50,\n61:   \"tags\": []\n62: }\n63: ```\n64: \n65: ### Claim Request JSON\n66: \n67: 领取申请 JSON 最小结构：\n68: \n69: ```json\n70: {\n71:   \"task_id\": \"任务 ID\",\n72:   \"agent_id\": \"申请 agent ID\",\n73:   \"model\": \"模型 ID\",\n74:   \"model_tier\": \"nano | cheap | standard | strong | expert\",\n75:   \"claim_reason\": \"领取理由\"\n76: }\n77: ```\n78: \n79: 模型等级顺序固定为：\n80: \n81: ```text\n82: nano < cheap < standard < strong < expert\n83: ```\n84: \n85: ### Markdown 领取门槛\n86: \n87: 前台 agent 生成或更新任务 Markdown 时，应包含类似小节：\n88: \n89: ```markdown\n90: ## 领取门槛\n91: \n92: 复杂度：中高\n93: \n94: 最低模型要求：strong\n95: \n96: 不建议使用：\n97: \n98: - nano\n99: - cheap\n100: \n101: 领取要求说明：\n102: \n103: 本任务涉及共享工具设计和多步骤判断，不允许低等级模型领取。\n104: ```\n105: \n106: ## Reviewer v0.1 Protocol\n107: \n108: 审核 agent 根据原始任务 Markdown 和执行 agent 提交的任务报告 Markdown 判断任务出口。\n109: \n110: 审核 agent 不执行任务、不运行验证命令、不修改产物，只做文本一致性判断。\n111: \n112: 审核结论只使用四类：\n113: \n114: ```text\n115: complete            任务已完全完成，下架并归入已完成\n116: return_to_agent     未完全完成，打回原 agent 继续\n117: relist_as_is        原任务仍合理，原样重新上架\n118: revise_and_relist   根据已完成部分和困难修订任务后重新上架\n119: ```\n120: \n121: 任务报告推荐结构：\n122: \n123: ```markdown\n124: # 任务报告\n125: \n126: ## 任务结论\n127: \n128: 完成 / 部分完成 / 受阻 / 无法完成\n129: \n130: ## 完成内容\n131: \n132: - ...\n133: \n134: ## 未完成内容\n135: \n136: - ...\n137: \n138: ## 产物路径\n139: \n140: - ...\n141: \n142: ## 验证结果\n143: \n144: - ...\n145: \n146: ## 遇到的问题\n147: \n148: - ...\n149: \n150: ## 是否需要继续\n151: \n152: - ...\n153: ```\n154: \n155: ## Status Model\n156: \n157: ```text\n158: draft      uploaded but not visible in the hall\n159: listed     visible and claimable\n160: claimed    claimed by an agent; hidden from the default hall view\n161: done       submitted as successful\n162: cancelled  cancelled by operator\n163: archived   hidden from normal active views\n164: ```\n165: \n166: 默认大厅视图只展示 `listed` 任务。领取后任务会进入 `claimed`，不会再出现在默认 `tasks` 列表里；需要看所有任务时用 `tasks all`，看已领取用 `tasks claimed`。\n167: \n168: ## Storage\n169: \n170: 默认状态目录位于本包内：\n171: \n172: ```text\n173: D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\mycli\\task-hall\\state\n174: ```\n175: \n176: 结构：\n177: \n178: ```text\n179: state/\n180:   listings.json\n181:   events.jsonl\n182:   requests/\n183:     req_xxx/\n184:       request.json\n185:       frontdesk.raw.txt\n186:       frontdesk-response.json\n187:   tasks/\n188:     task_xxx/\n189:       task.md\n190:       meta.json\n191:       claims.jsonl\n192:       submissions.jsonl\n193:       claim-review-yyyymmdd_hhmmss.json\n194:       submission-review-yyyymmdd_hhmmss.json\n195:       task-report-yyyymmdd_hhmmss.md\n196: ```\n197: \n198: ## Current Implementation Progress\n199: \n200: 当前已落地并测试通过：\n201: \n202: - `submit-request` 会调用 `agent-cli` 运行 `opencode/task-hall-frontdesk`。\n203: - 前台 agent 审核任务请求 JSON；通过后生成包含 `## 领取门槛` 的 `task.md`。\n204: - `submit-request` 默认创建并上架 `listed` 任务；使用 `--draft` 可只创建草稿。\n205: - `claim` 默认调用 `opencode/task-hall-frontdesk` 审核领取申请；通过后才进入 `claimed`。\n206: - `review-submission` 调用 `opencode/task-hall-reviewer` 审核任务报告。\n207: - 审核结论 `complete` 会把任务置为 `done`；`relist_as_is` 会重新上架；`revise_and_relist` 会更新 `task.md` 并重新上架；`return_to_agent` 只记录审核结果并要求原 agent 继续。\n208: - `tasks all --json` 可输出 JSON 列表。\n209: \n210: 前台与审核 agent 配置文件：\n211: \n212: ```text\n213: C:\\Users\\38188\\.config\\opencode\\agent\\task-hall-frontdesk.md\n214: C:\\Users\\38188\\.config\\opencode\\agent\\task-hall-reviewer.md\n215: ```\n216: \n217: 已知边界：\n218: \n219: - `task-hall` 只触发前台/审核 agent 做语义判断，不负责任务执行调度。\n220: - skill 不作为第一版硬性领取条件。\n221: - 领取申请最稳方式是提供 `claim.json`，避免 PowerShell 参数透传歧义。\n222: - 前台/审核 agent 返回 JSON 的稳定性依赖其 prompt；脚本会保存 raw output 和解析后的 JSON 以便排错。\n223: \n224: ## Usage\n225: \n226: ```powershell\n227: mycli task-hall init\n228: \n229: mycli task-hall submit-request D:\\agent_workspace\\tmp\\task-request.json\n230: mycli task-hall submit-request D:\\agent_workspace\\tmp\\task-request.json --draft\n231: mycli task-hall claim task_20260424_210000_abc123 opencode/private-assistant D:\\agent_workspace\\tmp\\claim.json\n232: mycli task-hall review-submission task_20260424_210000_abc123 D:\\agent_workspace\\tmp\\task-report.md\n233: \n234: mycli task-hall upload D:\\agent_workspace\\tmp\\task.md custom 50 workspace \"整理下载目录\"\n235: mycli task-hall upload-publish D:\\agent_workspace\\tmp\\task.md custom 50 workspace \"整理下载目录\"\n236: \n237: mycli task-hall tasks\n238: mycli task-hall tasks listed\n239: mycli task-hall tasks claimed\n240: mycli task-hall tasks all\n241: mycli task-hall show task_20260424_210000_abc123\n242: \n243: mycli task-hall publish task_20260424_210000_abc123\n244: mycli task-hall edit task_20260424_210000_abc123 \"新标题\" custom 80 \"tag1,tag2\" D:\\agent_workspace\\tmp\\new-task.md\n245: mycli task-hall claim task_20260424_210000_abc123 opencode/private-assistant D:\\agent_workspace\\tmp\\claim.json\n246: mycli task-hall claim task_20260424_210000_abc123 opencode/private-assistant --no-frontdesk\n247: mycli task-hall release task_20260424_210000_abc123 opencode/private-assistant\n248: mycli task-hall submit task_20260424_210000_abc123 success opencode/private-assistant \"完成说明\"\n249: mycli task-hall submit task_20260424_210000_abc123 fail opencode/private-assistant \"失败原因，会自动重新上架\"\n250: mycli task-hall done task_20260424_210000_abc123 opencode/private-assistant \"completed\"\n251: \n252: mycli task-hall cancel task_20260424_210000_abc123\n253: mycli task-hall delete task_20260424_210000_abc123\n254: mycli task-hall archive task_20260424_210000_abc123\n255: mycli task-hall status\n256: ```\n257: \n258: `submit-request` 会调用 `mycli agent-cli run --agent opencode/task-hall-frontdesk`，把任务请求 JSON 交给前台 agent 审核。审核通过后自动创建 `task.md` 任务并默认上架；带 `--draft` 时只创建草稿。\n259: \n260: `claim` 默认会调用前台 agent 审核领取申请。若要手动绕过前台审核，可使用 `--no-frontdesk`，但只建议维护者在测试或修复异常时使用。\n\n(Showing lines 1-260 of 665. Use offset=261 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# task-hall\n\n当前任务前台协议版本：`frontdesk-v0.2`\n\n`task-hall` 是面向 agent 的任务大厅。它只负责任务从“提交/上传”到“上架、展示、领取记录、报告审核、关闭或重新上架”的生命周期，不负责执行任务，也不主动调度任务。\n\n## Design\n\n任务大厅支持三类任务请求来源：\n\n- `scheduled`：定时定点发布到大厅的任务。\n- `trigger`：外部条件满足后发布到大厅的任务；条件检查由用户自定义 trigger 负责。\n- `custom`：手动上传和上架的临时任务。\n\n任务请求入口推荐使用 JSON；通过前台 agent 审核后生成 Markdown 任务说明文件，推荐命名为 `task.md`。任务正文、约束、交付物、验收标准和领取门槛以 Markdown 为主体。\n\n前台 agent 与审核 agent 配置位于：\n\n```text\nC:\\Users\\38188\\.config\\opencode\\agent\\task-hall-frontdesk.md","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"agent_workspace\\capability-library\\mycli\\task-hall\\README.md","time":{"start":1777074016647,"end":1777074016678}},"id":"prt_dc1dd9183001cCk2BgVn14mYuR","sessionID":"ses_23e23a62affeOLCYKs5at8IiBV","messageID":"msg_dc1dd44ef001kVrCHLqkpcf6ae"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1777074016722,"sessionID":"ses_23e23a62affeOLCYKs5at8IiBV","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_aB2rjpH1brpiRjpiiY3JDJWz","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\mycli\\project-manager\\README.md","limit":220,"offset":1},"output":"<path>D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\mycli\\project-manager\\README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # project-manager\n2: \n3: ## Summary\n4: \n5: Register, query, and manage durable agent projects in `D:\\agent_workspace`.\n6: \n7: `project-manager` uses per-project `.agent-project/project.json` files as source of truth and a generated global `registry.json` as a query cache.\n8: \n9: ## Commands\n10: \n11: ```powershell\n12: mycli project-manager init <project-root> --id <id> --name <name> --type <type> --mode finite|ongoing\n13: mycli project-manager register <project-root>\n14: mycli project-manager scan [roots...]\n15: mycli project-manager refresh [roots...]\n16: mycli project-manager list\n17: mycli project-manager query [filters]\n18: mycli project-manager get <id-or-name>\n19: mycli project-manager status <id-or-name>\n20: mycli project-manager update-status <id-or-name> [status fields]\n21: mycli project-manager task-list <id-or-name>\n22: mycli project-manager task-add <id-or-name> --title <title>\n23: mycli project-manager task-update <id-or-name> <task-id> [fields]\n24: mycli project-manager next-list <id-or-name>\n25: mycli project-manager next-add <id-or-name> --title <title>\n26: mycli project-manager next-update <id-or-name> <next-id> [fields]\n27: mycli project-manager context-add <id-or-name> --title <title> --phase <phase>\n28: mycli project-manager context-list <id-or-name> [--phase <phase>]\n29: mycli project-manager context-get <id-or-name> <context-id>\n30: mycli project-manager current <id-or-name>\n31: mycli project-manager agent-guide <id-or-name> [--phase <phase>]\n32: mycli project-manager maintenance-guide <id-or-name>\n33: mycli project-manager native <args...>\n34: ```\n35: \n36: ## Command details\n37: \n38: ### Initialize and register\n39: \n40: ```powershell\n41: mycli project-manager init <project-root> --id <id> --name <name> --type <type> --mode finite|ongoing [--register]\n42: mycli project-manager register <project-root>\n43: mycli project-manager scan [roots...]\n44: mycli project-manager refresh [roots...]\n45: ```\n46: \n47: `init` creates `.agent-project/project.json`, `status.md`, and support directories. Use `--register` to immediately add the project to the global registry.\n48: \n49: ### Query\n50: \n51: ```powershell\n52: mycli project-manager query --name <text>\n53: mycli project-manager query --type capability\n54: mycli project-manager query --mode ongoing\n55: mycli project-manager query --lifecycle active --phase operations\n56: mycli project-manager query --health red --attention needs_maintenance\n57: mycli project-manager query --tag automation\n58: mycli project-manager query --json\n59: ```\n60: \n61: Supported filters include `--id`, `--name`, `--type`, `--mode`, `--owner`, `--domain`, `--priority`, `--tag`, `--registration`, `--lifecycle`, `--phase`, `--activity`, `--health`, `--delivery`, `--attention`, `--last-run-status`, `--stale`, and `--missing`.\n62: \n63: ### Maintain status\n64: \n65: ```powershell\n66: mycli project-manager update-status <id> --lifecycle active --phase construction --activity in_progress --summary \"...\"\n67: ```\n68: \n69: ### Maintain tasks and next actions\n70: \n71: ```powershell\n72: mycli project-manager task-add <id> --title \"Implement feature\" --type implement --priority high --set-current\n73: mycli project-manager task-list <id>\n74: mycli project-manager task-update <id> task-0001 --status done\n75: \n76: mycli project-manager next-add <id> --title \"Run validation\" --type validate --set-current\n77: mycli project-manager next-list <id>\n78: mycli project-manager next-update <id> next-0001 --status done\n79: ```\n80: \n81: ### Dynamic context and agent handoff\n82: \n83: Use dynamic context to record stage-specific assumptions, requirements, feasibility findings, architecture notes, validation results, operation notes, and maintenance rules.\n84: \n85: ```powershell\n86: mycli project-manager context-add <id> --title \"Architecture decision context\" --phase architecture --type architecture --summary \"Use file-based registry first\" --file README.md --tag registry\n87: mycli project-manager context-list <id> --phase architecture\n88: mycli project-manager context-get <id> context-0001\n89: ```\n90: \n91: When an agent team takes over a project, start with:\n92: \n93: ```powershell\n94: mycli project-manager current <id>\n95: mycli project-manager agent-guide <id>\n96: mycli project-manager agent-guide <id> --phase validation\n97: mycli project-manager maintenance-guide <id>\n98: ```\n99: \n100: `agent-guide` prints project management rules, current status, open tasks, open next actions, and dynamic context for the requested phase.\n101: \n102: ## Examples\n103: \n104: ```powershell\n105: mycli project-manager init D:\\agent_workspace\\projects\\daily-hot-news --id daily-hot-news --name \"每日新闻热点收集\" --type research --mode ongoing --register\n106: mycli project-manager query --mode ongoing\n107: mycli project-manager query --lifecycle active --phase operations\n108: mycli project-manager query --attention needs_user_decision\n109: mycli project-manager get daily-hot-news\n110: mycli project-manager status daily-hot-news\n111: mycli project-manager update-status daily-hot-news --health yellow --activity degraded --attention needs_maintenance\n112: mycli project-manager task-add daily-hot-news --title \"Fix source parser\" --type maintenance --priority high --set-current\n113: mycli project-manager next-add daily-hot-news --title \"Check tomorrow's scheduled run\" --type operation_check --set-current\n114: ```\n115: \n116: ## Important fields\n117: \n118: - `project_mode`: `finite | ongoing`\n119: - `lifecycle`: `proposed | planned | active | paused | completed | retired | archived`\n120: - `phase`: `intake | requirements | feasibility | architecture | planning | construction | validation | launch | operations | maintenance | retirement | closure`\n121: - `activity`: `queued | in_progress | scheduled | stable | running | waiting | blocked | degraded | paused | needs_attention`\n122: - `health`: `green | yellow | red | gray`\n123: - `delivery`: `none | concept | draft | prototype | usable | delivered | verified | published | deprecated`\n124: \n125: Rule: ongoing projects should not be marked `completed`; they eventually become `retired`.\n126: \n127: ## Storage\n128: \n129: Per-project truth:\n130: \n131: ```text\n132: {project-root}\\.agent-project\\project.json\n133: ```\n134: \n135: Global registry cache:\n136: \n137: ```text\n138: D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\mycli\\project-manager\\registry.json\n139: ```\n140: \n141: If registry and project files disagree, trust `project.json` and run `mycli project-manager refresh`.\n\n(End of file - total 141 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# project-manager\n\n## Summary\n\nRegister, query, and manage durable agent projects in `D:\\agent_workspace`.\n\n`project-manager` uses per-project `.agent-project/project.json` files as source of truth and a generated global `registry.json` as a query cache.\n\n## Commands\n\n```powershell\nmycli project-manager init <project-root> --id <id> --name <name> --type <type> --mode finite|ongoing\nmycli project-manager register <project-root>\nmycli project-manager scan [roots...]\nmycli project-manager refresh [roots...]\nmycli project-manager list\nmycli project-manager query [filters]\nmycli project-manager get <id-or-name>\nmycli project-manager status <id-or-name>\nmycli project-manager update-status <id-or-name> [status fields]","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"agent_workspace\\capability-library\\mycli\\project-manager\\README.md","time":{"start":1777074016706,"end":1777074016721}},"id":"prt_dc1dd9188001xFo0xGSsanOBc0","sessionID":"ses_23e23a62affeOLCYKs5at8IiBV","messageID":"msg_dc1dd44ef001kVrCHLqkpcf6ae"}}
